Two detector telescopes were
mounted inside the scattering chamber on rotatable
arms on opposite sides of the beam direction in the
same reaction plane. Only the telescope, used to
measure the 3He, 4He as well as the 6He particles.
It consisted of two silicon surface-barrier (dE)
detectors of thickness 27.6 and 522 mu-m, respectively,
and a NaI (E) stopping detector. The stopping E detecto
had a NaI(Tl) crystal of 76 mm in diameter and 127 mm
in thickness. It had a HAVAR entrance window of 63.5mm
in diameter and 7 mu-m in thickness.

cyclotron facility of iThemba LABS
A target of 93Nb with a thickness of 1.05 mg/cm2 was
used. The target foil was mounted on an aluminium frame
with a 25 mm diam. aperture. The target frame was
mounted onto an aluminium ladder, which fits into a
target driving mechanism at the centre of the
scattering chamber.
